"10. In matters of this kind the court must have regard 
to Section 112 of the Evidence Act. This section is 
based on the well-known maxim pater is est quem 
nuptiae demonstrant (he is the father whom the 
marriage indicates). The presumption of legitimacy is 
this, that a child born of a married woman is deemed 
to be legitimate, it throws on the person who is 
interested in making out the illegitimacy, the whole 
