"Section 112 lays down that if a person was born 
during the continuance of a valid marriage between 
his mother and any man or within two hundred and 
eighty days after its dissolution and the mother 
remains unmarried, it shall be taken as conclusive 
proof that he is the legitimate son of that man, unless 
it can be shown that the parties to the marriage had 
no access to each other at any time when he could 
have been begotten. This rule of law based on the 
dictates of justice has always made the courts 
incline towards upholding the legitimacy of a child 
unless the facts are so compulsive and clinching as 
to necessarily warrant a finding that the child could 
